## R Data Setup


```r
library(dplyr)
library(jsonlite)
library(magrittr)
library(reshape2)
library(tibble)
library(tidyverse)

multidate <- function(data, formats){
  a<-list()
  for(i in 1:length(formats)){
    a[[i]]<- as.Date(data,format=formats[i])
    a[[1]][!is.na(a[[i]])]<-a[[i]][!is.na(a[[i]])]
  }
  a[[1]]
}

send_df_to_js <- function(df){
  cat(
    paste(
    '<script>
      var data = ',toJSON(df),';
    </script>'
    , sep="")
  )
}
```

<script src="d3.v4.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.1.1.min.js"></script>

<div id = "viz"></div> 

<script type="text/javascript">
var point_vals = d3.select("#viz")
  .append("p")
  .attr("align", "center")
  .text("Let's Begin.");
  
//Get how wide our page is in pixels so we can draw our plot in it
var page_width = $("#did-it-work").width();

// parse Time
var parseTime = d3.timeParse("%Y-%m-%d");
data.forEach(function(d) {d.date = parseTime(d.date); })
  
// set the dimensions and margins of the graph
var margin = 30,
    width = page_width - 2*margin,
    height = page_width*0.8 - 2*margin;

// Find max data values**
var x_extent = d3.extent(data, d => d.date);
var y_extent = d3.extent(data, d => d.adjClose);

// Set the scales 
var x = d3.scaleLinear()
  .domain(x_extent)
  .range([0, width]);
  
var y = d3.scaleLinear()
  .domain(y_extent)
  .range([height, 0]);

// The color
var color = d3.scaleOrdinal(d3.schemeCategory20);

// The line 
var	valueline = d3.line()
	.x(function(d) { return x(d.date); })
	.y(function(d) { return y(d.adjClose); });

//Set up our SVG element
var svg = d3.select("#viz").append("svg")
    .attr("width", width + 2*margin)
    .attr("height", height + 2*margin)
  .append("g")
    .attr("transform",
          "translate(" + margin + "," + margin + ")");

var bounce_select = d3.transition()
    .duration(1000)
    .ease(d3.easeElastic.period(0.4));

// Nest entries by stock ID    
var dataNest = d3.nest()
        .key(function(d) {return d.ID;})
        .entries(data);

var legendSpace = height/dataNest.length;

// Loop through each stock
    dataNest.forEach(function(d, i) {
        svg.append("path")
            .attr("class", "line")
            .style("stroke", function() {return d.color = color(d.key);})
            .style("stoke-width", 9)
            .style("fill", "grey")
            .style("fill-opacity", 0.0)
            .attr("id", 'tag'+d.key.replace(/\s+/g, ''))
            .attr("d", valueline(d.values));
        svg.append("text")
            .attr("x", page_width - (margin*2) + 5)
            .attr("y", (legendSpace/2)+i*legendSpace)
            .attr("class", "legend")
            .style("fill", function() {return d.color = color(d.key);})
            .on("click", function() {
                var active = d.active ? false:true
                newOpacity = active ? 0 : 1;
                d3.select("#tag"+d.key.replace(/\s+/g, '')) 
                    .transition().duration(100)
                    .style("opacity", newOpacity);
                d.active = active;
            })
            .on("mouseover", function() {
                if(d3.selectAll("#tag"+d.key.replace(/\s+/g, '')).style("fill-opacity") == 0) {
                    d3.selectAll("#tag"+d.key.replace(/\s+/g, ''))
                      .transition()
                      .duration(50)
                      .style("fill-opacity", 0.2);
                }
            })
            .on("mouseout", function() {
                if(d3.selectAll("#tag"+d.key.replace(/\s+/g, '')).style("fill-opacity") != 0) {
                    d3.selectAll("#tag"+d.key.replace(/\s+/g, ''))
                      .transition()
                      .duration(1000)
                      .style("fill-opacity", 0.0);
                }
            })
            .text(d.key);
    });
    
// Add the X Axis
svg.append("g")
    .attr("class", "axis")
    .attr("transform", "translate(0," + height + ")")
    .call(d3.axisBottom(x)
        .tickFormat(d3.timeFormat("%Y")))
    .selectAll("text")
        .style("text-anchor", "end")
        .attr("dx", "-.8em")
        .attr("dy", ".15em")
        .attr("transform", "rotate(-65)");

// Add the Y Axis
svg.append("g")
    .attr("class", "axis")
    .call(d3.axisLeft(y));
</script>
